name: Photography Changes Everything
description: I had been collecting images of stickers people posted around for a while before I came upon this one. Something about the graphical design in the real world re-digitised through the camera piqued my interest. I find myself endlessly fascinated by what you can make the light do through assemblies of glass to produce an image. The process seems pointed in two directions, with light coming in from the outside, and then the manipulation of the recording to alter the light coming back out again in the form of the image. The Photography changes everything. |  3366x2404px | 1/160s | Canon 400D and Lightroom | Photographed 30th September 2018 somewhere along Southampton Street, Brighton.
